main event: Two unidentified objects were sighted approximately 10 miles from Midway Island on May 27, 1960.
interesting points: The first object was observed for approximately 300 seconds before making a sudden move to the north,60 seconds later, another object was sighted on the same course,The objects were estimated to have speeds of 1200 to 3000 mph and no sound or trails were observed,The weather was clear with no air traffic reported at the time of the sighting,The analysis sheet requested further information but did not receive a response, preventing a valid conclusion.
